#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:128
msgid ""
"This function only works for real arrays. Complex arrays are NOT handled.  "
"It also works for multi-component arrays.  However, only 1, and 2 "
"dimensional arrays are supported. This function is very efficient, so large "
"arrays should not be a problem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:134
msgid ""
"If the second argument is set to 1, the array is deep-copied from from "
"numpy. This is not as efficient as the default behavior (shallow copy) and "
"uses more memory but detaches the two arrays such that the numpy array can "
"be released."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:139
msgid ""
"WARNING: You must maintain a reference to the passed numpy array, if the "
"numpy data is gc'd and VTK will point to garbage which will in the best case "
"give you a segfault."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:143
msgid "Parameters:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:145
msgid "num_array   a 1D or 2D, real numpy array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:142
msgid ""
"Given a subclass of vtkDataArray, this function returns an appropriate numpy "
"array containing the same data -- it actually points to the same data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:146
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:148
msgid "vtk_array   The VTK data array to be converted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/numpy_support.py:149
msgid ""
"Returns a list of 1-D numpy arrays (one per component), each zero-copy "
"sharing memory with the underlying VTK buffer."
msgstr ""

